# Claude Control Plane

`CLAUDE.md` is the canonical repository entry point. `AGENTS.md` and `.codex/manifest.md` are compatibility shims.

## Read Order

1. `.claude/config/runtime.yaml`
2. `README.md`
3. `.claude/config/project-surfaces.yaml`
4. `.claude/config/quality-gates.yaml`
5. `.claude/config/review-scope.yaml`
6. `.claude/config/trigger-derivation.yaml`
7. `.claude/config/finding-contract.yaml`
8. `.claude/config/workflow.yaml`
9. `.claude/config/reviewers.yaml`
10. `.claude/policies/quality.md`
11. `.claude/policies/review-scope.md`
12. `.claude/policies/finding-quality.md`
13. `.claude/policies/release-readiness.md`

If Agent Lightning is enabled or the task is about optimization, then continue with:
14. `.claude/policies/lightning-boundaries.md`
15. `.claude/config/lightning.yaml`
16. `.claude/config/telemetry.yaml`

## Control Surfaces

- `.claude/config/runtime.yaml`: project metadata, model defaults, and scope-memory defaults
- `.claude/config/project-surfaces.yaml`: explicit declaration of whether real model, prompt, or data-contract surfaces exist yet
- `.claude/config/quality-gates.yaml`: authoritative local QA commands, coverage, and blocked-state handling
- `.claude/config/review-scope.yaml`: authoritative delta/full review rules and milestone triggers
- `.claude/config/trigger-derivation.yaml`: deterministic mapping from change metadata to normalized review triggers
- `.claude/config/finding-contract.yaml`: canonical reviewer finding payload, field semantics, and example
- `.claude/config/workflow.yaml`: graph-friendly execution loop for scope, implementation, QA, triage, and remediation
- `.claude/config/reviewers.yaml`: config-driven reviewer registry with activation rules
- `.claude/config/lightning.yaml`: optional Agent Lightning optimization boundaries, objectives, and trainable surfaces
- `.claude/config/telemetry.yaml`: passive telemetry capture rules and export paths for optimization data
- `.claude/agents/`: detailed role definitions used by the workflow
- `.claude/policies/`: mandatory guardrails, finding quality rules, release-readiness checks, optimization boundaries, and escalation rules
- `.claude/memory/`: SQLite schema and retention conventions for scope memory

## Design Intent

- Keep Claude focused on the project control plane first.
- Keep AGENTS/Codex compatibility without duplicating the full control plane.
- Keep application code discovery targeted to the files relevant for the current task.
- Preserve a durable record of scope decisions so triage can anchor every decision to explicit prior intent.
